				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
					<p data-path-to-node="3"><b data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="0">Guida Pinot Grigio</b> is an elegant and refreshing white wine, renowned for its vibrant and balanced profile. It is the perfect choice for those seeking a light beverage with clear fruity notes, ideal for enjoying in warm weather or as an accompaniment to sophisticated dinners. It stands out for its citrus freshness and a clean finish on the palate.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="4,0,0"><b data-path-to-node="4,0,0" data-index-in-node="0">Brand:</b> Guida<br /><b data-path-to-node="4,1,0" data-index-in-node="0">Type of Drink:</b> White Wine (Pinot Grigio Varietal)<br /><b data-path-to-node="4,2,0" data-index-in-node="0">Origin:</b> Italy (Delle Venezie region)<br /><b data-path-to-node="4,3,0" data-index-in-node="0">Special Feature:</b> Features a light straw color with greenish reflections. It is noted for its aromas of green apple, pear, and subtle floral notes. It is a &#8220;crisp&#8221; wine, meaning it has a balanced acidity that cleanses the palate.<br /><b data-path-to-node="4,4,0" data-index-in-node="0">Alcohol Grade:</b> Typically between 12% and 12.5% ABV.<br /><b data-path-to-node="4,5,0" data-index-in-node="0">Content:</b> 750 ml<br /><b data-path-to-node="5,0" data-index-in-node="0">Disclaimer:</b> Please consume alcohol responsibly. Excessive alcohol consumption can lead to health problems. You must be of legal drinking age to purchase and consume alcoholic beverages in your country. Do not consume if pregnant or suspecting pregnancy. Check packaging for accurate ingredient list information.</p>
