				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
					<h3 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default"><a href="https://megawineandspirits.com/cotes-de-angeline-cote-de-provance-rose-750ml/">COTES DE ANGELINE Cote de Provance Rose 750ml</a></h3>				</div>
				</div>
				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-e61ef64 elementor-widget elementor-widget-theme-post-content" data-id="e61ef64" data-element_type="widget" data-e-type="widget" data-widget_type="theme-post-content.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
					<p data-path-to-node="3"><b data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="0">Côtes de Angeline</b> is a premium rosé wine that embodies the classic elegance of the Provence region. It is a delicate, dry, and highly aromatic wine, famous for its characteristic &#8220;onion skin&#8221; or pale pink hue. It is the very essence of the French summer, offering a sophisticated and refreshing experience that transports you directly to the French Riviera.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="4,0,0"><b data-path-to-node="4,0,0" data-index-in-node="0">Brand:</b> Côtes de Angeline<br /><b data-path-to-node="4,1,0" data-index-in-node="0">Type of Drink:</b> Rosé Wine<br /><b data-path-to-node="4,2,0" data-index-in-node="0">Origin:</b> Provence, France (AOC Côtes de Provence)<br /><b data-path-to-node="4,3,0" data-index-in-node="0">Special Feature:</b> Produced under the prestigious protected designation of origin, it stands out for its mineral freshness and notes of small red fruits (strawberry, raspberry) with a hint of peach. It is a silky, well-balanced wine with vibrant acidity.<br /><b data-path-to-node="4,4,0" data-index-in-node="0">Alcohol Grade:</b> Typically between 12.5% and 13.5% ABV.<br /><b data-path-to-node="4,5,0" data-index-in-node="0">Content:</b> 750 ml<br /><b data-path-to-node="5,0" data-index-in-node="0">Disclaimer:</b> Please consume alcohol responsibly. Excessive alcohol consumption can lead to health problems. You must be of legal drinking age to purchase and consume alcoholic beverages in your country. Do not consume if pregnant or suspecting pregnancy. Check packaging for accurate ingredient list information.</p>
