			<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-93e1fb2 e-con-full e-flex e-con e-parent" data-id="93e1fb2" data-element_type="container" data-e-type="container" data-settings="{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}">
		<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-e9266e8 e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child" data-id="e9266e8" data-element_type="container" data-e-type="container">
				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-0bbe2c4 elementor-widget elementor-widget-theme-post-title elementor-page-title elementor-widget-heading" data-id="0bbe2c4" data-element_type="widget" data-e-type="widget" data-widget_type="theme-post-title.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
					<h3 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default"><a href="https://megawineandspirits.com/ron-ron-ron-zacapa-xo-750-ml/">ZACAPA XO 750 ml</a></h3>				</div>
				</div>
				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-e61ef64 elementor-widget elementor-widget-theme-post-content" data-id="e61ef64" data-element_type="widget" data-e-type="widget" data-widget_type="theme-post-content.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
					<p>Zacapa XO is an ultra-premium Guatemalan rum, crafted from the first pressing of sugar cane, known as &#8220;virgin sugar cane honey.&#8221; Its distinctive aging process takes place using the Solera System at an altitude of 2,300 meters above sea level, in American oak barrels that previously aged robust whiskeys, delicate sherries, and fine Pedro Ximénez wines. A final aging stage in French oak barrels that previously held Cognac gives it a unique balance of complex aromas and flavors. Zacapa XO presents notes of dark chocolate, cherries, toasted nuts, marzipan, and orange peel, with a long, smooth, and sweet finish with hints of dried mango, raspberry, and ginger. It is an exquisite rum to enjoy neat or on the rocks, and it pairs wonderfully with dark chocolate and desserts.</p>
<p><strong>Brand:</strong>: Zacapa<br />
<strong>Origin:</strong>: Guatemala<br />
<strong>Quantity:</strong>: 750 ml<br />
<strong>Disclaimer :</strong> Please consume alcohol responsibly. Excessive alcohol consumption can lead tohealth problems. You must be 21 years of age or older to purchase and consume alcoholicbeverages in the United States. Do not consume if pregnant or suspecting pregnancy.</p>
				</div>
				</div>
